Aim:
To write a C++ program that implements multilevel inheritance.

Algorithm:
Start program.
Create a base class.
Create a second class derived from base class.
Create a third class derived from the second class.
Create an object of the last class.
Access members from all three classes.
Display the output.
End program.

Program:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
class A {
public:
    void displayA() {
        cout << "Class A method\n";
    }
};
class B : public A {
public:
    void displayB() {
        cout << "Class B method\n";
    }
};

class C : public B {
public:
    void displayC() {
        cout << "Class C method\n";
    }
};

int main() {
    C obj;
    obj.displayA();
    obj.displayB();
    obj.displayC();
    return 0;
}

Output:
Class A method
Class B method
Class C method

Result:
Multilevel inheritance was successfully demonstrated.
